name: coconut oil production, crude | coconut oil, crude | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/6093/documentation

data based on the ECOSOL study of the European surfactant industry. Allocations in multioutput processes were made, using the relative mass outputs of products.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



This module contains material and energy input, production of waste and emissions for the steps from the harvested coconuts to the crude coconut oil (i.e. the coconut halving, extraction of water, meat removal & shell production, drying and the oil extraction). Water consumption and infrastructure have been estimated.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/104:Manufacture of vegetable and animal oils and fats/1040:Manufacture of vegetable and animal oils and fats

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data based on coconut oil mills in Phillippines
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average technology, typical for Phillippines conditions in the mid 90s
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: data out of ECOSOL study of European Surfactant Industry. Common translation rules used, reported in Chemical report (Althaus et al. 2003). This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography PH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
